==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Minion
<hw>Min"ion</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>mignon</ets>, fr. OHG.
<ets>minni</ets> love, G. <ets>minne</ets>; akin to E. <ets>mind</ets>.
See <er>Mind</er>, and cf. <er>Mignonette</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A loved one; one highly esteemed and favored; -- in
a good sense.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God's disciple and his dearest <qex>minion</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Sylvester.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Is this the Athenian <qex>minion</qex> whom the world⟦br⟧
Voiced so regardfully?</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An obsequious or servile dependent or agent of
another; a fawning favorite.</def> <rj><au>Sir J. Davies.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Go, rate thy <qex>minions</qex>, proud, insulting boy!</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Print.)</fld> <def>A small kind of type, in size
between brevier and nonpareil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>⟦hand⟧ <miniontype>This line is printed in <it>minion</it>
type.</miniontype>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>An ancient form of ordnance, the caliber of which
was about three inches.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Beau. &
Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Minion</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Minion
<hw>Min"ion</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See 2d <er>Minion</er>.]</ety>
<def>Fine; trim; dainty.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Their . . .
<xex>minion</xex> dancing.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Fryth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Minionette</ent>⟦br⟧
